{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place sugar, water and cinnamon in mixing bowl then heat <b>10 min\/100°C\/\/speed 2<b>.","Place 15-20 ice cubes in a large bowl, top up with water, then set a slightly smaller bowl inside it. Pour syrup into smaller bowl and stir in orange liqueur. Continue to stir to cool the mixture and once lukewarm, stir in Seville orange juice.","Strain liquid through a fine sieve into a shallow freezer proof container then freeze overnight or for at least 10 hours.","Remove from freezer, tip out and cut into squares (3 cm x 3 cm). Place half the frozen squares in mixing bowl and churn <b>10 sec\/speed 6<b>. Add remaining frozen squares and churn <b>10 sec\/speed 6<b>. Transfer sorbet back into container and freeze for 3 hours. Serve straight from freezer."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["250 g granulated sugar","300 g water, plus more for cooling","2 cinnamon sticks, cut in 2.5 cm pieces","15 - 20 ice cubes, for cooling","3 Tbsp orange liqueur, e.g. Cointreau","200 g Seville orange juice"]}],"id":"r95894","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-j8fc55ooTEs\/XZanOTXcr7I\/AAAAAAAAg8A\/zUSFEopBSeUeMysxstrIfbiCaeZMNDCOgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_7dj-_-RM0wYQ9lZD.png","title":"Seville Orange Sorbet","publishedAt":"2015-09-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"0.2 g","fat":"0 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"47.9 g","calories":"805 kJ \/ 193 kcal"},"usefulItems":"small bowl, large bowl, fine sieve, freezer proof container, long sharp knife, freezer","hintsAndTricks":["Freeze the ice cream mixture in ice cube trays rather than cutting into squares if preferred.","This sorbet can also be made with naval oranges when Seville oranges are not in season. Decrease sugar by 75 g, or to taste."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","3h 25m","6 portions"]}